  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "OPAL coupling. Granular clouds detune the partial bank — the choir shatters into a thousand tiny fragments, each grain carrying a piece of the voice. OPAL's frequency modulation pushes partials off their integer ratios, creating inharmonic spectra that still carry the ghost of the vowel formant. Glass and breath. A stained glass window made of voice.",
